Step 1:
go to /home/{username}      #for me it's '/home/rsk'

Step 2:
Create a .desktop file (You can set your own custom name)      #for it's 'Auto Cut EX.desktop'

IMPORTANT: locate your auto-editor with terminal, use: which auto-editor (we will use the result in the next step)

Step 3: 
Copy and paste them;
[Desktop Entry]
Name=Auto Cut EX
Comment=Edit videos automatically
Exec={paste the location here}            #for me it's '/home/rsk/AutoCut/autoeditor-direct.sh'
Icon={you can make an icon}               #i made one with photoshop (svg) then put it in the same place as the .sh file, for me it was '/home/rsk/AutoCut/autocut.svg'
Terminal=true
Type=Application
Categories=AudioVideo;

## my version:
[Desktop Entry]
Name=Auto Cut EX
Comment=Edit videos automatically for Premiere Pro
Exec=/home/rsk/AutoCut/autoeditor-direct.sh
Icon=/home/rsk/AutoCut/autocut.svg
Terminal=true
Type=Application
Categories=AudioVideo;


Step 4: run this in terminal
chmod +x ~/Desktop/Auto\ Cut\ EX.desktop
mv ~/Desktop/Auto\ Cut\ EX.desktop ~/.local/share/applications/
